40520b11754eba7b56d4","tid":765840,"uid":76115,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-04T05:55:47.000Z","msg":"打delusions falling asleep搵到, 應該係佢<br />\n<br />\nHypnagogia, also referred to as &quot;hypnagogic hallucinations&quot;, is the experience of the transitional state from wakefulness to sleep: the hypnagogic state of consciousness, during the onset of sleep (for the transitional state from sleep to wakefulness see hypnopompic)<br />\n<br />\nThought processes on the edge of sleep tend to differ radically from those of ordinary wakefulness. <strong>For example, something that you agreed with in a state of Hypnagogia may seem completely ridiculous to you in an awake state.</strong> Hypnagogia may involve a &quot;loosening of ego boundaries ... openness, sensitivity, internalization-subjectification of the physical and mental environment (empathy) and diffuse-absorbed attention.&quot;[19] Hypnagogic cognition, in comparison with that of normal, alert wakefulness, is characterized by heightened suggestibility,[20] illogic and a fluid association of ideas.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypnagogia\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FHypnagogia&d=3qbCDYsWA4zLZmsCRWad2MVakpCEQgWe3bOYm8oES40%3D&h=6404f607\" target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypnagogia</a>"},{"pid":"2cdab7ea2b227e41ff8117d5198052b3ea3279b9","tid":765840,"uid":76115,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"2dc0717bf03f403d6f4386d87dfd6d8146b61605","tid":765840,"uid":67553,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d19fce07f7da73a4a1412ef71b888636f1d440c0","tid":765840,"uid":73572,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"2dfc4a9eca85b315c91487b9869ebe77966d993a","tid":765840,"uid":67553,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-03T13:48:15.000Z","msg":"迫自己起身寫低落本簿度<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-03T13:53:27.000Z","msg":"寫低有咩用<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-03T13:59:16.000Z","msg":"得閒睇返，會發現諗到好多平時諗唔到/唔會諗嘅嘢<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 個人會多好多諗頭"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-04T05:57:31.000Z","msg":"根據維基呢段野你應該講得啱<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nThe hypnagogic state can provide insight into a problem, the best-known example being August Kekul&eacute;&rsquo;s realization that the structure of benzene was a closed ring while half-asleep in front of a fire and seeing molecules forming into snakes, one of which grabbed its tail in its mouth.[23] Many other artists, writers, scientists and inventors &mdash; including Beethoven, Richard Wagner, Walter Scott, Salvador Dal&iacute;, Thomas Edison, Nikola Tesla and Isaac Newton &mdash; have credited hypnagogia and related states with enhancing their creativity.[24] A 2001 study by Harvard psychologist Deirdre Barrett found that, while problems can also be solved in full-blown dreams from later stages of sleep, hypnagogia was especially likely to solve problems which benefit from hallucinatory images being critically examined while still before the eyes."},{"pid":"30314fd758dcfeaa576ba8060f9dfa5cd8a6db4b","tid":765840,"uid":76115,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-04T16:15:13.000Z","msg":"你地幾歲開始會咁?<br />\n我係呢年幾先有, 今年廿頭<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f59c861799f5529eaa42f6e5547df9b6e76d2f5a","tid":765840,"uid":46500,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-05T03:52:08.000Z","msg":"好正常 人就係要喺空廢時期先有大量嘅創造力<br />\n<br />\n我寫小說都係喺去廁所同訓前先諗到好橋"},{"pid":"a3c20c71d017e52ec0c48b59e1c224f8928d6370","tid":765840,"uid":87397,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"30314fd758dcfeaa576ba8060f9dfa5cd8a6db4b","tid":765840,"uid":76115,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-04T16:15:13.000Z","msg":"你地幾歲開始會咁?<br />\n我係呢年幾先有, 今年廿頭<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-05T23:38:12.000Z","msg":"我都係差唔多21歲先開始咁<br />\n通常只會知自己亂諗野<br />\n一訓醒就無記憶"},{"pid":"8fcb267a80e089ccb68c22631c4a3697451f3a3c","tid":765840,"uid":49626,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-06T00:38:19.000Z","msg":"估唔到有人一樣<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n而家一開始諗就知要準備訓著"},{"pid":"e71f1afa5d68ca2e74b3f721c4a6e02b02d901e7","tid":765840,"uid":12152,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-06T01:37:40.000Z","msg":"冇你地咁痴線<br />\n但一訓落張床 合埋眼時<br />\n個腦就會出現好多神奇 好創作性既畫作<br />\n平時正常情況下叫我諗係絕對諗唔到<br />\n曾經試過想即刻起身畫底<br />\n因為畫功問題 自己支筆呈現唔到果畫面<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"548049f70ec980cba559375cb1a51e88dce9b2b9","tid":765840,"uid":137768,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-06T17:28:58.000Z","msg":"我臨訓反而諗野會忽然清晰好多 好似會無啦啦諗到有趣嘅ideas 解決到日頭諗唔通嘅野"}]}